nmrglue  (vendor FID file I/O)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
nmrglue: Helmus, J. J.; Jaroniec, C. P. "Nmrglue: an open source Python package
for the analysis of multidimensional NMR data." J. Biomol. NMR 55, 355-367 (2013).
DOI: 10.1007/s10858-013-9718-x
Source: https://github.com/jjhelmus/nmrglue
License: BSD-3-Clause.

nmrglue is an OPTIONAL dependency installed via the ``fid`` extra
(``pip install nmrcheck[fid]``). It is used solely for reading vendor-native
raw-FID file formats -- Bruker (``fid`` + ``acqus`` + ``procs``) and
Varian/Agilent (``fid`` + ``procpar``) -- and for the universal-dictionary
(``udic``) ppm-axis scaling used by ``moltrace.spectroscopy.io.fid_reader`` and
``nmrcheck.fid``. Reading vendor file formats for interoperability is
descriptive use; vendor trademarks (Bruker, Varian, Agilent) appear in this
product only as format-identifier strings and are not used in product branding.

nmrglue is not vendored; the dependency is pinned in ``pyproject.toml`` and
installed from PyPI, so its BSD-3-Clause copyright and license notice remain
intact at the package source.

