SciPy  (signal processing, optimisation, sparse linear algebra, interpolation)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
SciPy: Virtanen, P.; Gommers, R.; Oliphant, T. E. et al. "SciPy 1.0:
fundamental algorithms for scientific computing in Python." Nat. Methods 17,
261-272 (2020).
DOI: 10.1038/s41592-019-0686-2
Source: https://scipy.org
License: BSD-3-Clause.

Used for:

* ``scipy.signal.find_peaks`` / ``peak_widths`` -- initial peak detection in
  ``moltrace.spectroscopy.peaks.gsd``;
* ``scipy.optimize.least_squares`` -- pseudo-Voigt deconvolution in
  ``nmrcheck.gsd``;
* ``scipy.sparse`` -- Whittaker asymmetric-least-squares baseline solver in
  ``moltrace.spectroscopy.preprocess.phase_baseline``;
* ``scipy.interpolate`` -- cubic-spline baseline interpolation.

Not vendored; installed from PyPI.

